messages.content: ComfyUI_Eagleshadow is a collection of custom nodes for ComfyUI, mostly created using GPT-4.
What does the 'Select Model 20' node in ComfyUI_Eagleshadow do?
The 'Select Model 20' node is a modified version of the ComfyRoll 'CR Select Model' node that allows loading 20 models instead of 5.
How does the 'Round Float to String' node in ComfyUI_Eagleshadow work?
The 'Round Float to String' node takes a floating-point number, rounds it to two decimal places, concatenates it with a provided string, and returns the resulting concatenated string.
What is the purpose of the 'Save Image To Folder' node in ComfyUI_Eagleshadow?
The 'Save Image To Folder' node takes an image, folder path, and file name as input, and saves the image to the specified folder using the provided filename.
What does the 'Fix Checkpoint Name' node in ComfyUI_Eagleshadow do?

The 'Fix Checkpoint Name' node takes a file path as input, extracts the checkpoint name by finding the substring between the last backslash (\) and the .safetensors extension, and returns the extracted checkpoint name as a string.
How is the 'Simple Load Image Batch' node in ComfyUI_Eagleshadow different from the Load Image Batch node in WAS Node Suite?

The 'Simple Load Image Batch' node is a stripped-down version of the Load Image Batch node from WAS Node Suite, with all extra functionality removed for faster performance. It is designed to be around 100 times faster while still providing the essential functionality.
What is the purpose of the 'Batch 12 Images' node in ComfyUI_Eagleshadow?
The 'Batch 12 Images' node takes 12 individual images as input and stacks them into a single batch tensor.
How does the 'Image Linear Gamma Composite Masked' node in ComfyUI_Eagleshadow work?

The 'Image Linear Gamma Composite Masked' node composites two images with optional resizing of the top layer and masking. It applies linear gamma correction before compositing and re-applies gamma correction afterward.
